<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98521295290442></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98521295290442><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98521295290442 style='color: darkblue;'>So far so good</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 21st 5:15 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was in SK killing bandits for faction, when someone shouted that the live grimrot was up. I quickly sent the guy a message, as he said that he was going to kill him, and he agreed to let me loot. Unfortunatley, by the time i had got there, the corpse had rotted, and it got zilch.  I then sat down immediatley to pick up camp, and about 2 hours later the ph spawed. he was a standing putrid skelleton standing under the little plat with nothing on top of it. I promptly killed him as soon as he spawned, and about 3 hours and 20 minutes later, the undead version of grim spawned. I buffed myself up with everything i had, and killed him and his pet.  His pet died with one nuke, and i then rooted grim, he died with about 3 shots of banish undead.  it took all of about 23 seconds to kill the both of em.  I was really excited, because he dropped both the scythe and the heart, and then i read the boards here, and found out it was wrong scythe...i proceeded to cry..heheh. I am hoping to get lucky with the live version as well, but i won't hold my breathe. btw, im a 49 cleric, so i will prob have to get lots of help to kill the live version if what i hear about him being magic resistant is true<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
