<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98460398444403></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98460398444403><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98460398444403 style='color: darkblue;'>My Experience With Grimrot</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 14th 4:06 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First, let me say that I do not claim to be an authority on this quest.  I have completed it once and will share my experience in case it may help others.  <br>This quest took me about 40 hours to camp give or take an hour.  I decided to follow the 5 am / 5 pm recommendation.  The first night I killed the place holder at 5 am 3 times.  I never got Grim to spawn.  The next morning when I woke up, I loged on just to check and see if he was up and the undead version of Grim was up.  I can't guarantee it was because of the time I killed it as there may have been others that came during the 8 hours I wasn't online but it is possible I guess.  I have two accounts (no I don't have a life) so I had my level 50 cleric and level 51 warrior camped there. I loaded my warrior and easily killed the undead Grim.  My cleric didn't even have to heal my warrior and my warrior had no buffs on at all.  <br>I then spent several long days camping Grim.  I was killing at 5 pm at that point.  I was about to log to go to dinner and was waiting on my last spawn since I was timing it.  Much to my surprise (after about 40 hours total) the live version spawned.  I loaded my warrior and had my cleric there for heals.  I had a friend who was there playing his 45 wizard and we engaged Grim.  He was MUCH tougher to kill.  I had to heal my warrior several times with Celestial Heal and my wizard friend nuked several times but was almost resisted every time.  I could be wrong but I think the only spell he landed was a fire based one.  If anyone is interested, leave a post and I will double check and respond later.  <br>When the live Grim spawns, he is in pally armor (which kind of surprised me).  The place holder is the standing putrid skeleton under the little ruin.  I don't believe that killing any of the other skeletons in the area helps to force the spawn.  I turned in about 30 bandit sashes, 700 gold pieces (2 at a time), and killed probably 100 or so putrid skeletons.  Killing the putrid skeletons gives you the faction you need for the quest so I recommend killing them the entire time you are there to work on your faction while you work on this quest.  I have also heard that you can turn in bone chips to Lance Nova.....(whatever his name is) instead of gold pieces.  I don't know that this is correct but it might be worth a shot.  You turn them in two at a time just like the gold pieces.  If this works, just loot all of the skellies that you kill and you can turn their bone chips in for faction too.  <br>Like someone mentioned before, there is a pestilence scythe that drops off of both the live and dead versions that is not the one you need for the quest.  Each of the items have to be no drop for the quest.  Also as mentioned before, if you go to the guy in the temple and say "I come to defend (protect, can't remember the exact wording) life" and he tells you about Grim, then you are high enough faction to turn in the items for the Aegis.  <br>I realize that this isn't a lot of new information, but I just wanted to say that at least the 5 pm thing worked for me and that there is a possibility that the 5 am worked too.  Unfortunately, I didn't pay attention to spawn time so I really can't say if they spawn at midnight or noon.  I hope this helps someone out with the quest though as this is a really good item.  If you have any questions please feel free to post them and I will answer them if I can.<br><br>Shalon Shadowwolf, 52 Druid<br>Keggar Dabrewmeister, 51 Warrior<br>Ruumm Forrezz, 50 Cleric<br>Mithaniel Marr Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
