<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98249193021420></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98249193021420><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98249193021420 style='color: darkblue;'>RE: Camped for 29 hours and need some help please</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 18th 5:25 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When approaching the camp, look out carefully. You'll see 'a skeleton' and 'a putrid skeleton' around. Notice that all 'a skeleton' are standing, while 'a putrid skeleton' are on the ground (seated).<br><br>Now, there's ONE putrid skeleton that does NOT sit on the ground, but remain standing. He's just below one of the small support. That putrid skeleton is the one you seek.<br><br>Now, when you check, he might not be there. Why? Because his spawn time is 3h20mn. Yes, over 3 hours! Now, there's a trick to it: if he spawns at midnight, he spawns as Lord Grimrot (undead). If he spawns at noon, he spawns as the live version. All other times, he spawns as the putrid skeleton. If you want a Lord Grimrot to spawn, kill him just before 6 (am for night spawn, pm for noon spawn), and come back three hours later... and hope no one took over the camp.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
