<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98147780930689></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98147780930689><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98147780930689 style='color: darkblue;'>Fuzzy Hints</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 6th 4:47 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just got this one so here are some hints:<br><br>It's a looooong camp.  The spawn varies from 3:10 - 3:35 with lots of PH's.  If the spawn is in the day you have a *chance* at the live Grimrot, if at night you have a *chance* for the undead Grimrot.  The best time to kill the PH is 5:00 am or 5:00 pm (EQ Time).  Don't believe the boards that say he has to spawn at 12:00 noon/midnight to get the real grimrot, that is not so.<br><br>As for faction, the single best way is to collect bandit sashes.  This will give you something to do between spawns.  There is a nice bandit camp due east of the grimrot spawn in SK and has about 10 spawn possitions.  Buy a lot of backpacks and go to town on these guys.  It's great faction AND great money, I turned in 30 bandit sashes and made over 100pp (after selling the bronze weapons).  Here's another fact I didn't learn until I did it -- you get XP for the sashes!  And good xp too.  At level 51 I received a full blue bub for 30 sashes.  That's the quivelent of 2 hours in an xp group (yes 51+ xp sucks).<br><br>Good luck with the camp, the best advice I have for you is to make it an around the clock camp (you can log out or sleep between PH's).  That way you always know when it'll spawn and you can be there ready to kill it.  To give you some idea of wait time, I killed him every 3 (or so) hours for 3 days straight (yes during the night as well).  So for me it was a VERY long camp.  Others have had better luck with the spawn, but it is random, there is no formula other than the Day/Night spawn.<br><br>-Fuz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
