<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98019088923998></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98019088923998><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98019088923998 style='color: darkblue;'>Grimrot</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1750><span id=>Ongle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 22nd 7:17 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I finally finished killing the two Grimrots this morning after spending 50 or 60 hours camping him on and off for a month (largest stretch was 15+ hours). The following is my opinion on the whole spawn thing.<br><br>There is only one spawn and one PH (always carries a rusty bastard sword and is the only standing putrid) in a fixed spawn place. I've read elsewhere that he can spawn in any of the putrid places, but this is not true. When Grimrot does spawn, the time of day decides if you get the live or undead version. The live always spawns during the day, and the undead during the night -- never the other way around. As I have seen observed elsewhere, the time that is considered "night" is shorter then the "day", so the live version seems to be more common.<br><br>I have killed the PH at 5am, 5pm, 12am, 12pm, at random times, and watched others kill it at 1am, 3am, 1pm, and 3pm -- all of which resulted in a PH excepting 3 spawns. I don't think there is anything special about these times except that the death of the PH determines the time of the next spawn. The spawn time seems (as observed on another board) to be 3 game days minus roughly 7 hours. So killing the PH at 5am will result in a 10pm spawn (meaning undead version, if he spawns), give or take a couple of game hours. <br><br>The PH that spawned the live Grimrot for me was killed at 12pm and resulted in a 7am spawn. The PH that spawned the undead Grimrot was killed at 5am and resulted in a 11pm spawn.<br><br>Also, I'm told that the quest can be shared, but that all parties much have the same super-high warmly faction. I do not know for a fact that it can be shared, but this is what I'm told.<br><br>I don't think killing the other putrids has any effect on the spawn whatsoever. But if you kill time by killing putrids then beware the Corrupt Guards of Qeynos. There is a nasty level 50 SK Corrupt Guard that hangs around the PoD in NQ sometimes. He has harm touch is killed me (level 50 cleric) with one melee hit (300+- as I recall) and harm touch.<br><br>As for the spawns themselves, the undead version seemed to have about 1k hp. Banish Undead and Sound of Force took him down 3/4. The second Banish Undead killed him.<br><br>The live version is much tougher. He must have close to, but not quite, 2k hp. He seems very resistant to cleric nukes, other classes have less trouble casting on him. I killed, or help kill, him twice. I found that my nukes were next to useless against him but that it was possible to melee him down, saving mana for self-heals. Pumice (sp) stones (purchasable) are useful for debuffing him -- he seems to like to cast some sort of steal strength or similar spell.<br><br>Building faction with the Priests of Life is pretty easy, but almost as boring as the camp. Find Novashine in North Qeynos (either at the temple or wandering around outside) and give him either 2gp or (and this is quicker) 4 stacks of 2 bone chips. Keep doing this until the you can receive the quest from Camlend Serbold.<br><br>Good luck...<br><br>O<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
