	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 15th 11:42 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello and thanks to all who have posted information here regarding this difficult, if not arduous, quest.  Without the information posted here, this quest would have been almost impossible, and i still haven't figured out how anyone unraveled the mysteries of the VERY specific timing.  Anyway, i feel obligated to share with you all my Grimrot experience, which thankfully was quick and easy :)<br><br>First thing to note, is that I heard that to get the version of Lord Grimrot you want (i.e. the live or the undead version) you need to kill the place holder at a specific hour of the day.  For the undead version, kill the STANDING putrid skellie PH at 5AM (eq time).  To get the live version to spawn, kill the ph at5pm (eq time).  <br><br>The way that I did this was to camp at the spawn site, and log on once in a awhilke throughout the day until the PH was up.  I then protected him as best I could until the appropriate eq time for the kill.  The biggest dangers to killing him early are other players wandering too close and aggroing him.  I then buffed myself to max (I am a 44 cleric) and medded to full and camped.<br><br>3.5 real time hours after the PH went down I made sure i was back on line, and BOTH times the approprite Grimrot spawn popped!!  That part may have been a tad lucky, hehe.<br><br>The undead version is a total, utter puss for a 44 cleric, he went down like a sack of potatoes.  For the live version, who is around level 37-38 and has about 1700 hp's, I did a quick search in the zone and found a 50 ranger who was willing to help me:  Most folks are definitely willing to help:)  The live version was tougher, I only nuked him twice (I had a 50 ranger helping me, remember :).  One time the nuke was partially resisted and the 2nd time it went through full.  I am confident that I could have taken Lord on my own, assuming the resistance was not full.<br><br>Anyway, loot the pestilence scythe (no drop version) from the live grim and the heart from the dead grim.<br><br>I hope this clears some things up :)  Don't just randomly kill the place holder or you are in for a LONG LONG camp.<br><br>good luck, and may Brell smile upon you :)<br><br>Anders Sacrifizen (level 44 cleric) The Tribunal<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
