	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have some interesting information about Multiquesting for this.<br><br>I have had the scythe for some time while a friend had the heart on a pali he doesnt play much. He offered to try and multi it with me. I felt that camping grim for 40+ hours without a dead spawn was about my limit so I agreed. If it didnt work, I would return in a month or two to try it again.<br><br>Something wierd happened though:<br><br>-He didnt have enough faction to do the quest.<br>-I had enough faction.<br>-We were grouped.<br>-When he handed in his heart, he received the aegis.<br><br>YES, let me say again that he did not have faction and only handed in heart and received his Aegis. We didnt realize and I handed in scythe also, after which he said "WTF, I got the aegis".<br><br>I saw his message before I handed in my peice so there was no error in which was first. He got his aegis without faction and handing in only the heart.<br><br>I then got extremely lucky last night and woke up at 4am to find a dead grim standing there. I handed in the heart and received my aegis. But, that doesnt prove a bug because the scythe I handed in 10 hours earlier might completed my quest.<br><br>One of two things happened here. Either someone handed Carmend a scythe before we got there (which was what we first figured on). Or, the quest is bugged in some way. I for one cant think of any reason why someone would hand a scythe in alone. If you knew enough to hand it to him, you would know that a heart is also needed.<br><br>I feel that the probability that the quest is bugged is greater than the one that someone handed in a scythe before us.<br><br>If anyone out there has a heart only *AND* is willing to take a chance I would like to hear how handing in the heart only worked out for you.<br><br>If anyone else out there multis I would also like to hear what happened. Let me know which persons involved had enough faction too please.<br><br>If you would like to ask me questions regarding this, send me a tell in Xegony as Aurelius.<br><br>If it is a bug, I am sure alot of people without the scythe will be very happy. Would be interesting to see if grouping with someone that has faction does anything also.<br><br>Thanks and I am sure people will be reluctant to try this. I am really asking those people who have kind of given up on the quest but have the heart. Maybe have a friend with live peice standing by in case the heart does nothing.<br><br>I hope some try this and post something.<br><br>Thanks<br><br>Aurelius <br>Circle of Vengeance<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
